<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,258,1111]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,547,258,283]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Description of female terminalia.</emphasis>
Posterior margin of T5 triangular, brown with gray microtrichosity and with a row of robust setae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[681,820,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 81–86" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[176,1406,197,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[173,1406,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 81–86. Peckia (Peckia) hillifera (Aldrich), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 81. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 82. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 83. Spermatheca in lateral view. 84. Abdomen in posterior view. 85. Abdomen in dorsal view. 86. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 79, 83–84 = 2 mm; 80 = 0.5 mm; 81 = 0.1 mm; 82 = 1 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456147/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 84–86</figureCitation>
). T6 divided into two halves, yellow, with golden microtrichosity and a row of robust setae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[895,981,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURES 81–86" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[176,1406,197,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[173,1406,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 81–86. Peckia (Peckia) hillifera (Aldrich), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 81. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 82. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 83. Spermatheca in lateral view. 84. Abdomen in posterior view. 85. Abdomen in dorsal view. 86. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 79, 83–84 = 2 mm; 80 = 0.5 mm; 81 = 0.1 mm; 82 = 1 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456147/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
). Spiracle 6 located on intersegmentary membrane, spiracle 7 located on T6. T8 absent (
<figureCitation box="[700,833,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 81–86" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[176,1406,197,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[173,1406,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 81–86. Peckia (Peckia) hillifera (Aldrich), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 81. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 82. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 83. Spermatheca in lateral view. 84. Abdomen in posterior view. 85. Abdomen in dorsal view. 86. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 79, 83–84 = 2 mm; 80 = 0.5 mm; 81 = 0.1 mm; 82 = 1 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456147/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 81, 84</figureCitation>
). Epiproct triangular, covered with fine setae. Cercus covered with long and fine setae. Hypoproct triangular, covered with fine setae (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1132,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 81–86" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[176,1406,197,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[173,1406,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 81–86. Peckia (Peckia) hillifera (Aldrich), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 81. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 82. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 83. Spermatheca in lateral view. 84. Abdomen in posterior view. 85. Abdomen in dorsal view. 86. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 79, 83–84 = 2 mm; 80 = 0.5 mm; 81 = 0.1 mm; 82 = 1 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456147/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
). ST6 square, covered with setae distally and with robust setae near posterior margin. ST7 square, with short, sparsely distributed setulae and a median depression. ST8 reduced, wider than long, with a row of median setulae and two pairs of robust, median setae (
<figureCitation box="[229,318,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 81–86" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[176,1406,197,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[173,1406,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 81–86. Peckia (Peckia) hillifera (Aldrich), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 81. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 82. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 83. Spermatheca in lateral view. 84. Abdomen in posterior view. 85. Abdomen in dorsal view. 86. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 79, 83–84 = 2 mm; 80 = 0.5 mm; 81 = 0.1 mm; 82 = 1 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456147/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae globular, with grooves and a small rounded chamber where they receive the spermathecal duct (
<figureCitation box="[369,453,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 81–86" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[176,1406,197,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[173,1406,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 81–86. Peckia (Peckia) hillifera (Aldrich), female from Pará, Bragança (MPEG). 81. Abdominal sternites and tergite 6 in ventral view. 82. Epiproct, cercus and hypoproct in apical view. 83. Spermatheca in lateral view. 84. Abdomen in posterior view. 85. Abdomen in dorsal view. 86. Abdomen in ventral view. Scale bars: 79, 83–84 = 2 mm; 80 = 0.5 mm; 81 = 0.1 mm; 82 = 1 mm. Abbreviations: CE = cercus; EP = epiproct; HP = hypoproct; ST = sternite; T = tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1456147/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
